“The Water’s Edge” is about taking a leap of faith and stepping outside of your comfort zone. 

I wrote it 2 years ago when @jefflandbee decided to take a leap of faith and quit a job that no longer served him. We were at Santa Monica beach, and he was planning on sending his resignation email that day. He told me he felt like he was standing at the edge of the water, and knew he’d be fine once he jumped in, but the fear of the cold was preventing him from taking the leap. I immediately knew I had to make a song about it and started writing the lyrics on the beach. And Jeff sent in his email that day. 💙

I have a message for you 💖

Stream “When The Fear Arrives” now on all platforms 🎵 One of the songs from my debut, self-produced album Ascend! 

We are so close to hitting 100k streams on the album 🤯🙏🏼

#432hzmusic #upliftingmusic #messageforyou #spirituality #ascend #femaleproducer #singersofig #producerdj #electronicproducer #indiehouse #electropop

2022 had many ups and downs, highs and lows, twists and turns, but I’m so grateful that I get to call this life mine! 

A few events that transpired in 2022:

• We said goodbye to Grandma’s physical avatar this year, but I know she’ll always be with me. 💖

• I traveled to Costa Rica for a “conscious creator” retreat with 10 strangers who turned out to be my soul family ✨

• I booked my first DJ gigs with @weekendtripmusic 🎵

• I was a hair model for @guy_tang , @wella , and @lanzahaircare 💇🏼‍♀️

• I published my first book, “Psychedelic Guide & Integration Journal” 🍄

• Had my first 1 Million view video on Tik Tok, and hit 65k followers on there ✨

• A video of mine on IG reels hit 5 million views, my new record 🤯

• I got to be a musical director for the first time ever for @alessa_marmo’s play at the Brisk Festival 

• I achieved one of my proudest accomplishments this year: Cheers to hitting 150k+ streams on my debut, self-produced album! And in only 2 months time 🤯 Honestly tho, the biggest accomplishment was simply finishing it and releasing it. 😅 The success it’s had and positive feedback Ive received is just a delicious cherry on top 🙏🏼

_____________

p.s. Here’s a friendly reminder that what you see on social media is only one fraction of a person’s life, and typically only includes the highlight reel. What you don’t see is all the hard work, days of stress and tears, and moments of existential crisis that occurred. Try not to compare yourself to others on Instagram, as we all have unique paths, and comparison is the thief of joy 😉

That said, I’m looking forward to all the ups and downs that 2023 is sure to bring! 

My intention/resolution for this new year is to lean deeper into trust and surrender, and to find a balance between work and play, action and rest. I also intend to release more new music and to collaborate with other artists! 

What’s your intention for 2023? 

#2022recap #independentartist #producerdj #happynewyear

I wrote this song a few years back when I was in the beginning stages of my awakening, and learning about all the ways in which our world is controlled by cultural hegemony and power structures. 

From the moment we are born, we are bombarded with all this “programming” and conditioning to live our lives a certain way, to be “good citizens”, a “good girl”, etc. 

I’ve always been one to reject social paradigms, however, and pave my own path. We don’t all have to follow the typical “go to school, get a 9-5, get monogamously married, have kids” lifestyle. 

Our souls crave to be free! 

I hope this song enlightens your perspective and inspires you to live an authentic life based in your own truth, not someone else’s. 💖

Along my self growth and spiritual journey, I have come to discover a few tools that have immensely helped me understand myself and to heal from/cope with the anxieties that come from living in a world that is so disconnected from our true nature. 

Amongst these tools are cannabis, yoga, meditation, affirmations, ecstatic dance, sound baths, breath work, qi gong, reiki, tarot/oracle cards, and other plant medicines. 💚

Each tool has its own special kind of magic that helps bring me deeper into the present moment, and back home to the heart and soul. ✨

After re-connecting to my own soul and healing so many of my fears/traumas/anxieties, I am passionate about helping others to do the same, whether that be through the messages in my music or through guiding people at my events. 💖

In grouping these spiritual modalities together for a day retreat, I’ve intuitively created an experience for you to join me in re-connecting to your higher self and building authentic connection in community. 

I am so excited and honored to lead you in my next event with @cosmicascensionguide ! This work truly fills my soul. And as a reminder, if you feel called to join, but are not a smoker, you are most certainly welcome to participate without cannabis! 

Early bird tickets will be available for 2 more days, and spots are filling up 🥰

More info & tickets can be found at the l!nk in my profile ✨

A meme thread on choosing to eat plants 🌱✨

I’m not one to tell you how to live your life, but I do think it’s valuable to share my perspective. I choose not to eat animals because I believe they are kind and sentient beings who do not deserve to suffer or die on our behalf, when it is perfectly possible (and efficient) to survive off plants. In fact, the strongest animals in the world, like elephants and gorillas, are plant eaters. 🦍🐘

I also understand that choosing a plant based diet is better for the planet, because we need an exponentially greater amount of crops to feed & fatten livestock before killing them than we would need to feed all humans. Cow production is actually also one of the biggest causes of CO2 emissions in our atmosphere. 🌎

I choose this lifestyle not only because of the animals and planet, but also for my own health. Red meat and processed meats are type 1 & 2 carcinogens (cancer causing), and have been linked to cardiovascular diseases. I for sure got way healthier when I went vegan—my skin problems cleared up, I became way less bloated, I get sick way less often than I used to, etc. 👌🏼

There are spiritual reasons as well—I believe that you are taking on the energetic karma of an animal’s suffering when you consume a being that has been caged, tortured, and anxious for most its life as it gets forced through a slaughter house. I don’t think most people know that female cows get forcibly impregnated to continue producing milk and babies that then get taken away from them. 😔🐮

I know so many people who say they are “animal lovers”, but continue to eat them. Would you eat your cat or your dog if you love them? Why not? 💖

I hope this post allows for some reflection. I know most people have good hearts and good intentions, but we’ve been fed a lot of misinformation and marketing propaganda to normalize the enslavement of “lesser” species so that corporations can profit off the abuse of animals. 

I’m very passionate about this topic and hope I can inspire more love in the world & a healthier planet 💖

Looking back on my 2023 💖 

A few key moments:
• my debut album independently surpassed 350K+ streams 🥳
• I got to perform so many places like @losglobos , @theenchantedloft , and @flowlifeglobal 🕺🏻
•  Released our first track together as @weekendtripmusic with @jefflandbee 😎
• DJ’d the after party for @outboundmammoth ‘s annual music series with @weekendtripmusic 
• modeled for @lanzahaircare at their global hair competition 
• hit 70K followers on Tik Tok 
• Went to some amazing shows like @deserthearts , @lsdream , and @alldayidream 
• published a gratitude journal 💖
• hosted two @cosmicascensionguide mini retreats 
• released two new singles “Trust in the Vision” and “Where I Intend to Go” with @spaceship.earth_music ✨
• made lots of memories with people I love 
• and so much more!

Also just a reminder that these are only my highlights, and there were also plenty of rough times and difficult moments that are not pictured on social media. I think we forget that sometimes and become way too hard on ourselves, comparing to other people’s lives. 

I’m looking forward to continuing to grow in 2024, and am so grateful to all my friends, family, and fans who have supported me along the way 🥰 🙏🏼
